# Router setup (when touching `main.tsx`)

- `createRouter`: `defaultPreload: "render"`, `scrollRestoration: true`, `notFoundMode: "root"`, `defaultErrorComponent` from `@/components/empty-states`, `context: { queryClient }`.
- Re-render on `i18n.on("languageChanged", …)` so Clerk `localization` stays aligned with locale.

# Root route (`__root.tsx`)

- Use `createRootRouteWithContext` with router context typing.
- Mount global providers, `setClerkGetToken`, one `<Toaster richColors />`, shared `NotFound` as `notFoundComponent`.

# Layout conventions

- `_app` + `_app/` — authenticated shell: sidebar, header, scope providers, Clerk `<Protect>`, redirect unauthenticated users to sign-in as already implemented.
- `_auth` + `_auth/` — sign-in/up; redirect signed-in users away per existing pattern.
- `_base` + `_base/` — public/marketing layout when present.

# Navigation and params

- Internal links: TanStack `<Link>`. Render redirects: `<Navigate … />`. Params: `Route.useParams()`.
- Do not use raw `<a href>` for in-app navigation.

# Auth model

- Clerk only—no custom JWT storage, refresh logic, or hand-rolled sign-in forms.
- Roles/permissions: fetched from `GET /access/:scopeId` via `useGetAccess(scopeId)` (`hooks/access`); response is a discriminated union (`AdminAccess | StaffAccess`) typed in `services/access/Access.api.ts`. UI gates like `access?.role === RoleTypes.ADMIN || (access?.role === RoleTypes.STAFF && access.permissions?.feature)`. Fail closed on undefined/401/403. Global capabilities (e.g. create-event) cannot be gated by this endpoint—render for any signed-in user. Treat all gates as UX only—backend is authoritative.

- Access grant management uses the grants endpoints under `/access/grants/:eventId`. Grant records are `AccessAccount` rows keyed by `clerkId`, and admin-only surfaces such as the access nav item render only for `RoleTypes.ADMIN`.

# Route modules

- Export: `export const Route = createFileRoute("…")({ … })` matching existing routes.
- Static segments kebab-case; dynamic `$param.tsx`; folder index `index.tsx`.
